26:32.056 --> 26:41.106
And when Dr. Gibson, this professor, was giving his words of thanks and appreciation at the unveiling of the beautiful portrait, he said this in the future,

26:41.986 --> 26:47.592
When people see this painting, they will ask the question, not, who is that man?

26:49.173 --> 26:52.617
But who painted that portrait?

26:53.998 --> 27:00.204
It was a way for him of expressing his appreciation at the artistic skill of the portrait maker.

27:01.185 --> 27:04.348
That's a picture, though, of what God is doing.

27:04.408 --> 27:10.034
You know, God's grace has been manifested to us, not so that we could become the center of attention

27:10.530 --> 27:16.838
Not so that we ultimately, well, people will walk around and have been saying, well, who is that man?

27:17.458 --> 27:19.160
Who is that woman?

27:20.102 --> 27:21.383
What about that man?

27:21.443 --> 27:22.765
Or what about that woman?

27:23.305 --> 27:29.573
But no, they'll say, who did that work of grace in him?

27:30.534 --> 27:33.798
Who did that work of grace in her?

27:33.858 --> 27:35.120
Who saved that man?

27:35.200 --> 27:36.641
Who saved that woman?

27:38.504 --> 27:40.466
We are his workmanship.

27:40.802 --> 27:47.632
created in Christ Jesus and for the display of God's grace.

27:48.614 --> 28:01.774
So because of his rich mercy and his great love and his immeasurable grace and kindness to us in Christ Jesus, he has made us alive in Christ Jesus and that is what this table before us is all about.

28:02.876 --> 28:04.338
On the night in which he was betrayed,

28:04.482 --> 28:09.650
just hours before his crucifixion, he gathered his disciples for one last supper.

28:09.690 --> 28:17.842
And he said to them, I have earnestly desired to eat this Passover with you before I suffer.

28:19.264 --> 28:20.145
And they didn't understand.

28:20.185 --> 28:32.203
They didn't understand yet that he was going to be the true Passover lamb who takes away their sin, that he was going to suffer in himself what their sins truly deserve.

28:32.264 --> 28:33.906
But Jesus knew

28:34.754 --> 28:36.376
And Jesus knew them.

28:36.416 --> 28:38.077
Oh, just think of them for a moment.

28:38.818 --> 28:41.140
And he didn't say all of what I'm about to say.

28:41.180 --> 28:49.168
We don't know the way in which his thoughts ran, but you can imagine it for a moment, can't you?

28:49.909 --> 28:54.833
Jesus sitting with them at supper and thinking, I know who you are.

28:56.155 --> 28:57.576
I know what you are like.

28:58.537 --> 28:59.338
I know you, Thomas.

29:00.619 --> 29:03.922
I know you're gonna doubt my resurrection, though I told you I would rise.

29:04.386 --> 29:18.691
I know you're going to doubt my promises to rise and I know that you're not going to believe any of these other men with whom we have spent three years together when they tell you I rose until you can touch my hands and my side after my resurrection.

29:19.012 --> 29:23.179
I know you doubting Thomas and I know you Matthew.

29:23.199 --> 29:29.490
I know who I chose by that seashore when I called it a tax collector to be mine.

29:30.146 --> 29:40.637
I know all your notorious tax collecting friends and the other sinners, the prostitutes, the wicked that you brought to that party to celebrate that I called you.

29:40.697 --> 29:41.859
But I knew who you are.

29:41.879 --> 29:43.541
I know you, Peter.

29:43.561 --> 29:47.925
I know you always speak without thinking.

29:49.026 --> 29:52.430
You have in mind the things of Satan, not the things of God.

29:53.411 --> 29:58.657
You're going to deny me to my face three times before I'm crucified, Peter.

29:58.677 --> 29:59.698
He'll tell him.

30:00.066 --> 30:01.007
He's going to do that.

30:02.389 --> 30:10.499
And I know you, all of you men, I know you're about to dispute with one another as they did about which of them is the greatest.

30:12.281 --> 30:19.550
I know that you're all going to fall asleep in the garden when I take you there and ask you to remain awake while I pray.

30:19.570 --> 30:24.997
I know you'll all scatter away from me when they come to arrest me.

30:26.299 --> 30:28.882
I know your courage will fail.

30:29.698 --> 30:43.476
And I'll have to confine you behind a locked door after my resurrection, because you think I'm still dead and buried, and you're worried about what trouble might come.

30:44.237 --> 30:56.754
I know all of this about all of you and worse, and I have eagerly desired to eat this meal with you.

30:59.330 --> 31:03.616
for I will give my body and my blood for your sins.

31:04.657 --> 31:09.623
Your salvation will be built not on the strength of your love and faithfulness to me.

31:09.663 --> 31:16.712
Your salvation will be built on the strength of my love and faithfulness to you.

31:16.752 --> 31:27.346
One day you'll eat this Passover and one day my people will continue to eat this Passover meal in remembrance of me.

31:28.610 --> 31:32.737
and the bread and the wine will speak to you that I loved you.

31:34.159 --> 31:55.314
And I gave myself for you eagerly and you will eat and drink bread and wine because I

32:01.058 --> 32:03.702
will eat the bread of affliction.

32:05.425 --> 32:22.532
And I will drink the cup of God's wrath because of my mercy, my love, and my grits, and my kindness toward you.

32:25.156 --> 32:28.882
What other rock can hold you?

32:30.242 --> 32:31.744
but the rock who is Christ.

32:33.106 --> 32:35.569
Oh, put your hopes in him.

32:35.589 --> 32:36.070
Let's pray.

32:49.869 --> 32:56.018
Father, heaven, thank you that the steadfast love of the Lord never ceases.

32:59.010 --> 33:06.063
And we ask by your spirit that we would know how wide and long and high and deep is the love of Christ.

33:08.687 --> 33:16.261
We ask that you would feed us, nourish us, strengthen us in His love.

33:17.763 --> 33:19.066
In Jesus' name I pray.

33:20.568 --> 33:20.909
Amen.

33:21.811 --> 33:22.051
Amen.

33:22.091 --> 33:23.794
Let's stand together and sing.

